'''Amokrane «Da Mokrane» Oualiken''' (April 6, 1933 – June 22, 2010) was an [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|football]] player and manager

==Career==
Oualiken was born in [[Ben Aknoun]], [[Algiers|Alger]], [[Algeria]].

He was a member of the [[Algeria]]n [[Algeria national football team|FLN team]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sebbar.oldiblog.com/designs/include/popup_photo.php?id%3D1664494%26nbl%3D74363 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-12-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110826225609/http://sebbar.oldiblog.com/designs/include/popup_photo.php?id=1664494&nbl=74363 |archivedate=2011-08-26 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aitbouhini.blog.ca/2005/08/03/da_mokrane |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-12-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081205003402/http://aitbouhini.blog.ca/2005/08/03/da_mokrane |archivedate=2008-12-05 |df= }}</ref> and played mostly as an attacking midfielder on the left wing.

Oualiken died on June 22, 2010 in [[Ben Aknoun]], [[Algiers|Alger]].<ref>http://www.elmoudjahid.com/accueil/societe/61180.html</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.letempsdz.com/content/view/40351/1/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-09-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713202553/http://www.letempsdz.com/content/view/40351/1/ |archivedate=2011-07-13 |df= }}</ref>

==Club career==
* 1945–1950 ''ES Ben Aknoun'' (Junior) {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1950–1951 [[MC Alger]] (Junior) {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1951–1952 [[MC Alger]] {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1952–1953 ''Corporative Hussein-Dey'' {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1953–1954 ''FSGT Seine-Saint-Denis'' {{flagicon|FRA}}
* 1954–1955 [[Tours FC]] {{flagicon|FRA}}
* 1955–1956 [[LB Châteauroux]] {{flagicon|FRA}}
* 1956–1957 ''FC Chartres'' {{flagicon|FRA}}
* 1957–1960 [[Nîmes Olympique]] {{flagicon|FRA}}
* 1962–1963 [[MC Alger]] {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1963–1969 [[USM Alger]] {{flagicon|ALG}}

==Coaching career==
* 1967–1969 [[USM Alger]] {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1969–1970 ''ES Ben Aknoun'' {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1970–1971 ''Union Sportive des Hospitaliers d'Alger'' {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1971–1977 [[JS El Biar]] {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1989–1990 [[MC Alger]] {{flagicon|ALG}}
* 1991–1992 [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]] {{flagicon|BFA}}

Oualiken was also coach of the football section of the Algerian Gendarmerie from 1969 to 1977. In 1977, he became the Technical Director of now defunct club [[DNC Alger]], helping the team climb from the amateur divisions up to the top flight and win the [[Algerian Cup]] in 1982.

==Honors==
* Member of the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian FLN National Team]]
* Has 5 caps for the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian National team]]
* Won the [[Algerian Championnat National]] once with [[USM Alger]] in 1963
* Three times [[Ligue 1]] runner-up with [[Nîmes Olympique]] in 1958, 1959 and 1960
* Finalist of the [[Coupe de France]] once with [[Nîmes Olympique]] in 1958

