{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}
'''Bipin Ganatra''' (born {{circa|1957}})<ref name=dna/> is an [[electrician]] in [[Kolkata]], [[West Bengal]], India. He is also an unofficial volunteer firefighter and was awarded the [[Padma Shri]] in 2017 for helping fight fires in the city.
== Inspiration == As a child Ganatra would rush after fire engines when he heard them and would start helping the firemen when he reached the scene of the fire. In 1982 Ganatra, then only 12 years old, lost his elder brother Narendra to a freak fire accident which occurred when a spark fell on fuel that his brother was handling while working on a motorcycle. His brother was admitted to hospital and succumbed to his injuries a little over a month later.<ref name=express/>
== Life == Ganatra, originally from [[Gujarat]], has been offering his services as a fireman in the city of [[Kolkata]], whose firefighting force of 1,258 firemen battled some 2,000 fires in 2014 and 1,600 fires in 2015.<ref name=bbc/> He is an electrician by trade and earns a meager salary, borrowing from his friends to make ends meet. He also helps the police manage traffic.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.india.com/news/india/meet-padma-awardee-bipin-ganatra-who-chases-fire-to-protect-people-1784739/|title=Meet Padma awardee Bipin Ganatra who chases fire to protect people|last=ANI|date=2017-01-26|work=India.com|access-date=2017-08-02|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802130424/http://www.india.com/news/india/meet-padma-awardee-bipin-ganatra-who-chases-fire-to-protect-people-1784739/|archivedate=2 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
Ganatra does not have any formal training with regards to firefighting. He started out by helping firefighters do odd jobs but now has risen to the level of a professional firefighter.<ref name=dna>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-padma-shri-winner-after-losing-his-brother-to-fire-at-age-of-12-this-man-has-spent-his-life-as-voluntary-fire-fighter-2296094|title=Padma Shri winner: After losing his brother to fire at age of 12, this man has spent his life as voluntary fire fighter|date=2017-01-25|work=Daily News & Analysis|access-date=2017-08-02|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802170501/http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-padma-shri-winner-after-losing-his-brother-to-fire-at-age-of-12-this-man-has-spent-his-life-as-voluntary-fire-fighter-2296094|archivedate=2 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Over 40 years, Ganatra has assisted in more than 100 fires, working to put out the flames, rescue victims, and clear away debris.<ref name=bbc>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-35557392|title=The Indian man who chases fires|last=Biswas|first=Soutik|date=2016-03-06|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-07-31|language=en-GB|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731113155/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-35557392|archivedate=31 July 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> One of his most dramatic rescues was of a pregnant woman trapped on the fifth floor of a burning building. The woman was too scared to move, so Ganatra scaled the building to reach her and convince her to come down.<ref name=express/> Ganatra has suffered injuries several times while helping put out flames, and also risked his life to extract two unexploded cylinders from a burning warehouse on [[Strand Road, Kolkata|Strand Road]].<ref name=express/>
Ganatra monitors the television news constantly and informs the fire department if a fire breaks out. Despite his contributions to the force he travels to the site by himself using public transport. In recognition of his efforts, the fire department has given him a rare steel volunteer card and a khaki uniform.<ref name=express>{{Cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/west-bengal-unofficial-firefighter-bipin-ganatra-to-get-padma-shri-4495257/|title=West Bengal: Unofficial firefighter Bipin Ganatra to get Padma Shri|date=2017-01-28|work=The Indian Express|access-date=2017-08-02|language=en-US|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730155227/http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/kolkata/west-bengal-unofficial-firefighter-bipin-ganatra-to-get-padma-shri-4495257/|archivedate=30 July 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
