{{Infobox Christian leader | type = bishop | honorific_prefix = His Excellency, the Most Reverend | name = Jean-Michel Faure | honorific_suffix = | title = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | church = | archdiocese = | province = | metropolis = | diocese = | see = | elected = <!-- or | appointed = --> | term = <!-- or term_start / term_end --> | quashed = <!-- or | retired = --> | predecessor = | successor = | opposed = | other_post = <!---------- Orders ----------> | ordination = 1977 | ordained_by = [[Marcel Lefebvre]] | consecration = March 19, 2015 | consecrated_by = [[Richard Williamson (bishop)|Richard Williamson]] | cardinal = | created_cardinal_by = | rank = <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = <!-- as birth_place --> | buried = <!-- or | tomb = --> | resting_place_coordinates = | nationality = French | religion = [[Roman Catholic]] | residence = | parents = | spouse = <!-- or | partner = --> | children = | occupation = | profession = <!-- or | previous_post = --> | education = | alma_mater = [[The International Seminary of Saint Pius X]] | motto = | signature = | signature_alt = | coat_of_arms = | coat_of_arms_alt = }} '''Jean-Michel Faure''' is a traditionalist Catholic bishop who is excommunicated from the Catholic Church.<ref name=Glatz>[http://www.catholicherald.co.uk/news/2015/03/19/bishop-williamson-is-excommunicated-after-illicitly-ordaining-a-bishop/ Glatz, Carol. "Bishop Williamson is excommunicated after illicitly ordaining a bishop", ''Catholic Herald'', 19 March 2015]</ref>
==Early life== In 1941, he was born to French [[Pied-Noir|pieds-noirs]] parents in [[Algiers]].
==Religious career== In October 1972 he joined the [[Society of St. Pius X|SSPX]] Seminary at [[The International Seminary of Saint Pius X|Ecône]] (Switzerland) and was ordained a priest by [[Marcel Lefebvre|Archbishop Marcel Lefebvre]] in 1977.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dominicansavrille.us/interview-with-fr-jean-michel-faure/|title=Interview with Fr. Jean-Michel Faure|work=Dominicans of Avrille, France}}</ref>
Soon after he was appointed at the head of the SSPX district for Southern America.{{cn|date=September 2017}}
In 1980 he was made the director of the SSPX Seminary in [[La Reja]] (Argentina).{{cn|date=September 2017}}
He was appointed at the head of the Mexican district in 1985.{{cn|date=September 2017}}
In 2013 he left the SSPX over the dispute of a possible agreement with Rome and joined the [[SSPX Resistance]].{{cn|date=September 2017}}
He was consecrated a bishop on March 19, 2015 by [[Richard Williamson (bishop)|Bishop Richard Williamson]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2015/03/18/vaticaninsider/eng/the-vatican/williamson-ordains-a-new-bishop-1WsZbTXQgVViHcHGIfPbJO/pagina.html|title=Williamson ordains a new bishop|date=18 March 2015|work=LaStampa.it}}</ref>
On March 19, 2016 he was co-consecrator of [[Bp Dom Tomás de Aquino Ferreira da Costa|Bishop Miguel Ferreira da Costa]], aka Fr Thomas Aquinas.{{cn|date=September 2017}}
