{{Infobox football biography | name = Koceila Berchiche | image = | caption = | fullname = Koceila Berchiche | birth_date = [[Beni Douala]], [[Algeria]] | birth_place = {{birth date and age|1985|8|5|mf=yes}} | height = | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[JSM Béjaïa]] | clubnumber = 5 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[JS Kabylie]] | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = [[MO Béjaïa]] | youthyears3 = | youthclubs3 = [[USM Alger]] | years1 = 2006–2008 | clubs1 = [[WA Rouiba]] | caps1 = - | goals1 = - | years2 = 2008–2011 | clubs2 = [[JS Kabylie]] | caps2 = 41 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2011–2014 | clubs3 = [[MC El Eulma]] | caps3 = 86 | goals3 = 4 | years4 = 2014–2015 | clubs4 = [[MC Alger]] | caps4 = 30 | goals4 = 2 | years5 = 2015–2017 | clubs5 = [[JS Kabylie]] | caps5 = 35 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2017–2018 | clubs6 = [[CA Bordj Bou Arreridj]] | caps6 = ? | goals6 = 0 | years7 = 2018– | clubs7 = [[JSM Béjaïa]] | caps7 = ? | goals7 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Algeria Military national football team|Algeria Military]] | nationalcaps1 = ? | nationalgoals1 = ? | medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{ALG}}}} {{MedalSport|Men's [[World Military Cup|Football]]}} {{MedalGold|[[2011 Military World Games|Rio 2011]]|[[World Military Cup - Men's tournament|Team Competition]]}} | club-update = 00:00, March 14, 2012 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 00:00, March 14, 2012 (UTC) }}
'''Koceila Berchiche''' (born August 5, 1985 in [[Beni Douala]]) is an [[Algeria]]n football player who is currently playing for [[JSM Béjaïa]] in the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 2]].<ref>[http://www.depechedekabylie.com/sport/55771-cest-reve-que-jouer-jsk.html La Dépêche de Kabylie<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.lirf.org.dz/effectif-2007-2008/war.htm Fiche de contrôle<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
==Club career== Berchiche started his career in the junior ranks for [[JS Kabylie]] but left to join [[MO Béjaïa]] and then [[USM Alger]]. His first senior side was [[WA Rouiba]] where he played for 2 seasons before joining [[JS Kabylie]] in the summer of 2008 on a free transfer.
==International career== Berchiche is a member of the [[Algeria national football team|Algerian Primary Team]].
==Honours== * Won the [[World Military Cup]] once with the '''Algerian National Military Team''' in 2011
