{{Infobox wheelchair tennis player | name = Marjolein Buis | image = Marjolein-buis-1350309763.jpg | caption = Buis at Wimbledon during 2012 | fullname = Marjolein Buis | country = {{NED}} | residence = Beuningen | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|01|11}} | birth_place = [[Nijmegen]], Netherlands | death_date = | death_place = | turnedpro = 2010 | retired = | plays = Right handed | coach = [[Wouter Kropman]] | careerprizemoney = | tennishofyear = <!-- year inducted into the Tennis Hall of Fame --> | tennishofid = <!-- ID from the Tennis HoF website, taken from http://www.tennisfame.com/hall-of-famers/First Name-Last Name i.e. martina-navratilova, which it is all undercase letters--> | website = | singlesrecord = | singlestitles = | highestsinglesranking = No.3 (21 May 2012) | currentsinglesranking = No.5 (9 July 2018) | AustralianOpenresult = SF (2011, 2012, 2013, 2016) | FrenchOpenresult = '''W''' (2016) | Wimbledonresult = SF (2016) | USOpenresult = SF (2013, 2014) | Othertournaments = yes | WheelchairTennisMastersresult = 3rd (2013) | Paralympicsresult = QF (2012) | doublesrecord = | doublestitles = | highestdoublesranking = '''No. 1''' (2012) | currentdoublesranking = No.2 (9 July 2018) | AustralianOpenDoublesresult = '''W''' (2016, 2018) | FrenchOpenDoublesresult = '''W''' (2012) | WimbledonDoublesresult = RU (2017) | USOpenDoublesresult = '''W''' (2017) | OthertournamentsDoubles = Yes | WheelchairTennisMastersDoublesresult = '''W''' (2017) | ParalympicsDoublesresult = [[File:Gold medal Paralympics.svg|20px|alt=|link=]] '''Gold Medal''' (2012), '''Silver Medal''' (2016) | updated = 12 April 2018<!-- adds date this template was last updated as an individual article --> }}
'''Marjolein Buis''' (born 11 January 1988) is a Dutch [[wheelchair tennis]] player. She participated in the [[2012 Summer Paralympics|Paralympic Games in London, 2012]], and won a gold medal in the women's doubles event with partner [[Esther Vergeer]]. Marjolein is the current (April 2018) World Number One in the doubles.<ref>http://www.itftennis.com/wheelchair/players/player/profile.aspx?playerid=100112310</ref>
Marjolein Buis was born in [[Nijmegen]], the Netherlands. At the age of 14 she started to experience problems when walking. It turned out that she has a connective tissue disorder, the [[Ehlers–Danlos syndrome]], which affects the stability of the joints. She would never be able to play able bodied sports again. At the age of 17, Marjolein discovered wheelchair tennis. In 2010, she graduated in Social Work and became a full-time tennis player. She qualified for the Paralympic Games in London 2012 and reached the quarter final in singles and won gold in doubles with her partner Esther Vergeer. At the Paralympic Games in Rio 2016 Marjolein reached the quarter final in singles again and this time won silver in doubles with her partner [[Diede de Groot]]. Marjolein is still a full-time player. In her spare time she studies Psychology.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/buismarjolein</ref>
